article.headline: Towson 84, VMI 69
article.story: LEXINGTON, Va. (AP) -- Jonathan Pease scored 25 points and Lawrence Hamm grabbed 15 rebounds Saturday as Towson snapped a 13-game road losing streak by beating VMI 84-69. Towson (3-6), which had lost five in a row overall, trailed only once -- at 5-4 on Reggie Williams' three-point play with 16:32 to go in the first half. Pease hit 3-pointers at both ends of a 30-8 run as the Tigers built a 34-13 lead with 3:46 left in the half. Towson led by 17 at the break, and VMI (4-2) could get no closer than 13 the rest of the way. Pease, who was 9-of-14 from the field and 5-of-10 from 3-point range, led all five Towson starters in double figures. Holden Plack scored 19, Hamm 14, Mike Green 12 and Trevan Jackson 11. Williams scored a career-high 28 for the Keydets. Matt Coward added 15 and Fred Robinson 10. Towson shot 54 percent from the field to VMI's 38 percent, and the Tigers outrebounded the Keydets 39-25.
